---
import Head from '../layouts/Head.astro';
import Scripts from '../layouts/Scripts.astro';
import HeroPynx      from '../components/secondary/HeroPynx.astro';
import Navbar    from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer    from '../components/Footer.astro';
import BackToTop from '../components/BackToTop.astro';
---

<Head title="PSON" heroid="ehs" description="PSON; The better JSON for Python." keywords="Inferno, PSON, BxPP, AT Products LLC" author="Alex Toucan & Pynx" />
<div id="page">
	<Navbar />
	<HeroPynx
		title="PSON for JSON"
		description="Made by Pynx&semi; PSON; the better JSON for Python."
		primaryHref="#downloads"
    primaryText="Downloads"
    secondaryHref="https://github.com/2983u2/Pson/"
    secondaryText="Source Code"
      dropdownItems={[
        { navigationDesc: "General Information", navigationLink: "#general-info" },
        { navigationDesc: "Requirements", navigationLink: "#requirements" },
        { navigationDesc: "Installation", navigationLink: "#install" },
        { navigationDesc: "Downloads", navigationLink: "#downloads" },
      ]},
    />
    <main id="bxpp" class="container">
		<div id="general-info">
			<h2> General Information </h2>
			<p>PSON aka PynxSON, made by Pynx, is a JSON extension for Python3. It uses a Python script as a library, then you create a Python script using functions from the library for it to create a JSON file using what you wrote.</p>
			<p>What does PSON have? Well:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>Comments (Ever needed to describe your objects? Well now you can!)</li>
        <li>Better read and write (no "with open")</li>
        <li>Better Speed and compatibility</li>
      </ul>
			<p>
				<b>Version:</b> 1.0 <br>
				<b>Platforms:</b> Windows, Linux, and MacOS.
      </p>
		</div>
    <hr>
    <div id="requirements">
      <h2> Requirements </h2>
      <p><b>Python:</b> 3.0 or above</p>
    </div>
		<hr>
		<div id="install">
			<h2> Installation </h2>
			<p>
        <ol>
          <li>Download the <a href="https://github.com/2983u2/Pson/blob/main/Pson.py">Python library file</a>.</li>
          <li>Import the file: <code>from Pson import *</code></li>
          <li>Call the functions: <b><u><a href="https://github.com/2983u2/Pson?tab=readme-ov-file#examples">Examples</a></u></b></li>
          <li>Run your script to generate a JSON file.</li>
        </ol>
			</p>
		</div>
		<hr>
		<div id="downloads">
			<h2>Downloads</h2>
			<div class="d-grid d-sm-flex gap-2">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/2983u2/Pson/blob/main/Pson.py">Library File (Python)</a> 
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="https://github.com/2983u2/Pson/archive/refs/heads/main.zip" download="">ZIP Download (Python)</a> 
      </div>
		</div>
	</main>
	<Footer author="Alex Toucan & Pynx" />
	<BackToTop />
</div>
<Scripts />
